{"TopicId":182544,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"single part that constantly rotates?","CreatedByName":"Jiraiyah","CreatedById":97667,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-01T11:49:26Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jiraiyah","CreatedById":97667,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-01T11:49:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m looking for a mod that provides a simple part with two nodes on both sides that rotates around itself when activated both clockwise and counter clockwise, this way, i would be able to attach any stationary part to it, and when desired, tell it to start the spin and have fun. I recall there was a part like this before, but no matter how much i try, can\u0027t find something like this any more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve_v","CreatedById":69272,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-01T12:09:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223549522\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182544\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551440966\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297667\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jiraiyah\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, Jiraiyah said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI recall there was a part like this before\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere was, around 1.0. Spin-o-tron or something like that.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe closest current mod I can think of is:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2404620656\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/170484-16-15-14-dockrotate-lightweight-robotics-rotational-control-on-docking-ports-plus-noderotate-make-any-part-rotate/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSet the rotation step to zero for continuous rotation.\u003Cbr\u003E\nYou could also use it\u0027s NodeRotate module to make yourself a custom rotating part if you don\u0027t want to use docking ports.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jiraiyah","CreatedById":97667,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-01T12:11:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223549529\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182544\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551442198\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steve_v\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, steve_v said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere was, around 1.0. Spin-o-tron or something like that.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe closest current mod I can think of is:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6400164920\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/170484-16-15-14-dockrotate-lightweight-robotics-rotational-control-on-docking-ports-plus-noderotate-make-any-part-rotate/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:225px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSet the rotation step to zero for continuous rotation.\u003Cbr\u003E\nYou could also use it\u0027s NodeRotate module to make yourself a custom rotating part if you don\u0027t want to use docking ports.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndidn\u0027t know setting the step to zero will do that. nice. thanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}